Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.22,0:00:07.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An encounter with this young girl is what inspired\NInspector Shiratori to become a police officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.58,0:00:12.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Inspector initially thought Detective Sato was that girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.22,0:00:17.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was actually our homeroom teacher,\NKobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}, that was his girl of memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.07,0:00:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} then came across a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.36,0:00:26.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was a pawn shop owner, Sumida Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.99,0:00:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was said to have angered many people\Nwith her vicious business practices.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.29,0:00:36.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s response to Inspector\NShiratori's questioning, we obtained three clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.50,0:00:40.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first being the angry voices of the culprit and the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.72,0:00:47.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The second being the stationary truck near the\Nscene, possibly from a moving company.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.43,0:00:50.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the third...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.14,0:00:55.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the silhouette of the culprit witnessed by Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.51,0:01:18.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we continue lamenting the passing seasons...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.49,0:01:20.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be unable to confront the mysteries of cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.35,0:01:22.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Shiratori and Kobayasi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.22,0:01:24.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What will the outcome be of the case and their love?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.34,0:01:26.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.10,0:01:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.14,0:01:29.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.27,0:03:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As—I—said!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.52,0:03:06.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was watching TV at home alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.03,0:03:08.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a soccer match I couldn't miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.62,0:03:12.88,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kagitani Kikuna (25)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.78,0:03:12.88,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,If it hadn't been for that, I would've gone to\Nthe culprit's place and killed her myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.24,0:03:15.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really hated her that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.00,0:03:17.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.04,0:03:21.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I needed money real bad, so I had to temporarily\Npawn my late mother's ring out of desperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.84,0:03:26.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't have enough money to buy it back in\Ntime, so I went to beg her for more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.05,0:03:28.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that woman was wearing my mother's ring and said...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.88,0:03:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Oh, about that cheap excuse for a ring, I already sold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.97,0:03:35.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"This one may look similar, but it's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.22,0:03:40.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"And it's worth twenty times more," without any hint of shame!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.69,0:03:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.60,0:03:43.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could I not want to kill her!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.02,0:03:45.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.49,0:03:47.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.29,0:03:51.50,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Takimoto Ryouko (31)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.80,0:03:51.50,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Are you thinking I was the one who killed her?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.91,0:03:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.03,0:04:00.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, on the day she was killed, I heard you took a day off from\Nthe restaurant you work at and slept alone at home, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.54,0:04:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it couldn't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.54,0:04:05.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My cold's gotten a lot worse lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.71,0:04:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.67,0:04:08.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's your relationship with the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.42,0:04:11.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We heard you really hate her...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.13,0:04:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I do not particularly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.72,0:04:17.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just that I bought a 500,000 yen antique plate from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.81,0:04:21.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it started smelling weird, so I hired an appraiser to check it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.98,0:04:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It turned out to be a replica, only worth 300 yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.65,0:04:29.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention that odor turned out to be cat food...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.28,0:04:33.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she'd only been using it as a dish to feed her cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.74,0:04:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't bear a grudge against her at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.79,0:04:44.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I did borrow some money.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.04,0:04:46.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About five million yen from that woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.79,0:04:52.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I finally secured a way to return it and we set up an agreement,\Nbut now that she's dead, I guess I can't repay her, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.89,0:04:58.15,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kodama Ryuusuke (27)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.28,0:04:56.93,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,As proof, at the time that woman was killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.96,0:05:00.86,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I had just polished off a bottle of premier\Nchampagne at home and got really drunk!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.18,0:05:04.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even the day before the murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.77,0:05:09.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was heard storming into your\Napartment and demanding her money back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.78,0:05:11.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was just for show, for show.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.15,0:05:15.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was just an excuse for her to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.62,0:05:17.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Too see the former hero of Koshien!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.37,0:05:23.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since I injured my left shoulder prior\Nto being drafted, I wasn't able to go pro.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.37,0:05:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody seems to remember me anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.00,0:05:26.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.25,0:05:30.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That chick was really into me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.92,0:05:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.84,0:05:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like we recorded the three suspects' voices perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.05,0:05:37.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.14,0:05:40.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now all we need is for Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} to check the voices.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.22,0:05:47.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if the culprit is female, that last guy is probably unrelated.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.31,0:05:50.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, what kind of person is that Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.61,0:05:53.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard from Yumi that she's got Shiratori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} in a fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.49,0:05:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's a teacher in Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s class at the elementary school.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.78,0:06:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems they had a chance meeting recently during a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.16,0:06:08.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I was sure Shiratori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} loved\Nsomeone from within this headquarters, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.25,0:06:09.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.30,0:06:13.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was you, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.55,0:06:16.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, can you introduce me to that Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.97,0:06:19.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it's best if I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.85,0:06:21.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why can't I meet her?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.56,0:06:24.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well... there are reasons...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.06,0:06:26.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What reasons, you're not answering my question!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.77,0:06:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just not a good idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.98,0:06:29.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, there really is!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.77,0:06:31.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone who looks just like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.86,0:06:33.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think her name was...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.48,0:06:35.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato Miwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.20,0:06:37.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How nice...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.95,0:06:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had wanted to be a policewoman too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.58,0:06:45.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, that bastard Takagi's flirting around again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.79,0:06:47.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With our Miwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.54,0:06:54.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soon after Shiratori dropped out, he started to run amok!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.76,0:07:02.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that guy was the chief executive of\NSato Miwako's Absolute Line of Defense!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.10,0:07:06.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I guess Shiratori's got some skill too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.43,0:07:10.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, to find a chick that looks exactly like Sato.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.15,0:07:13.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if that look-alike is around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.23,0:07:15.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He simply settled for that Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.53,0:07:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.03,0:07:19.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}, sorry for the wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.66,0:07:24.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.29,0:07:26.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.79,0:07:33.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"This one may look similar, but it's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.88,0:07:38.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"And it's worth twenty times more," without any hint of shame!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.88,0:07:40.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.09,0:07:41.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could I not want to kill her!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.30,0:07:47.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was the voice of the first suspect, Kagitani Kikuna{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.15,0:07:52.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the next one...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.81,0:07:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention that odor turned out to be cat food...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.61,0:08:00.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she'd only been using it as a dish to feed her cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.66,0:08:03.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't bear a grudge against her at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.08,0:08:08.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the voice of the second suspect, Takimoto Ryouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.04,0:08:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the next one would be the third suspect, Kodama Ryuusuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.79,0:08:17.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since he's a male, he probably isn't relevant to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.88,0:08:19.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But just in case...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.26,0:08:21.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he was irrelevant, then just forget about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.97,0:08:27.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.18,0:08:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, after hearing the voices of the two\Nwomen, did either of them sound familiar?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.06,0:08:38.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did one of them have a voice similar to the\Nculprit's bellowing you heard at the scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.82,0:08:46.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For ease of reference, I've chosen the parts\Nwhere they were most emotionally excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.87,0:08:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.04,0:08:51.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.50,0:08:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you hear the culprit's voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.33,0:08:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think either of those voices matches the culprit's.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.80,0:09:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I heard was a deeper, intimidating woman's voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.97,0:09:06.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.14,0:09:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you need to either find a new suspect...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.35,0:09:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or locate and interview the passengers of the vehicle\Nresembling a moving truck that drove past me at the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.77,0:09:18.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that truck...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.07,0:09:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We couldn't locate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.82,0:09:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We couldn't find any trucks with a big "09" printed on the side.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.53,0:09:27.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.95,0:09:31.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it possible that you misread the numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.50,0:09:37.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they were partially blocked by the wall,\Nthen a 5 could be mistaken for a 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.71,0:09:40.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just because they're alike, doesn't mean that I would mistake them!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.96,0:09:41.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.01,0:09:44.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Not me"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.76,0:09:45.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.76,0:09:51.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible the employees happened to stop\Ntheir truck for reasons unrelated to business.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.52,0:09:57.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course we also thought of that and pressed them, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.23,0:10:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even after also interviewing people living in the vicinity...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.03,0:10:07.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems no one ordered a moving or a shipping truck to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.70,0:10:09.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.74,0:10:16.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was only making up this information so that I\Ncould have fun fooling around with you police!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.58,0:10:18.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.92,0:10:20.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.63,0:10:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already told you what I saw and heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.88,0:10:26.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.05,0:10:28.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allow me to drive you home...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.89,0:10:31.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In case you encounter the suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.10,0:10:34.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.93,0:10:37.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can at least take care of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.60,0:10:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So would you stop bothering me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.23,0:10:43.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.03,0:10:45.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiratori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.03,0:10:48.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.45,0:10:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Shiratori, I think it's best if she has escort.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.58,0:10:57.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since Sensei was spotted by the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.17,0:10:59.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.25,0:11:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chiba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, can I leave that to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.63,0:11:03.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.55,0:11:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.42,0:11:06.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.51,0:11:09.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like I'm being hated.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.30,0:11:13.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}, please wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.52,0:11:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.02,0:11:20.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would Sensei be mad at you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.52,0:11:22.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you say something bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.48,0:11:23.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dunno...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.98,0:11:26.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only one reason it could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.28,0:11:30.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} may have seen Detective Sato earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.66,0:11:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} saw Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.83,0:11:40.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition, if she happened to hear rumors about\Nyour infatuation for Detective Sato...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.17,0:11:43.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei will definitely suspect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.38,0:11:48.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"That Inspector Shiratori was only being nice\Nto me because I look like Detective Sato.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.88,0:11:52.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Am I just a substitute for Detective Sato?" she may think.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.15,0:11:54.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.31,0:11:56.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was never a substitute...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.06,0:11:58.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} is my girl of destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.81,0:12:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you also once mistook Detective\NSato for your girl of destiny, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.19,0:12:06.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I won't deny that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.73,0:12:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be better if you told her already?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.90,0:12:17.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} is your girl of destiny from childhood,\Nthat you saved in that bookstore from those shoplifters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.41,0:12:20.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course I want to tell her the truth, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.04,0:12:23.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just can't seem to find the right timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.17,0:12:26.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yo, Inspector-in-love!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.63,0:12:29.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd it go with the suspects' voices?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.05,0:12:30.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She heard them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.22,0:12:32.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.68,0:12:35.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they don't seem to match what she heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.72,0:12:36.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.72,0:12:37.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.60,0:12:40.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's this teacher that's been giving Shiratori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} butterflies?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.98,0:12:45.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wants to meet her no matter what...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.90,0:12:46.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiratori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.17,0:12:49.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.36,0:12:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like it isn't the right time... for this...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.25,0:13:11.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.01,0:13:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.51,0:13:14.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei, see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.47,0:13:15.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.51,0:13:17.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's dangerous to run!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.26,0:13:19.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.85,0:13:24.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei doesn't look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.73,0:13:29.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess she still hasn't heard anything about\Nbeing Inspector Shiratori's girl of destiny, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.61,0:13:32.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, how about I tell her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.91,0:13:34.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.41,0:13:37.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not romantic unless he tells her himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.79,0:13:39.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if you say so...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.79,0:13:42.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this keeps up she'll never be able to know!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.08,0:13:45.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not so bad, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.37,0:13:50.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike some big liar who's been hiding\Nhis identity from someone he loves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.30,0:13:50.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.46,0:13:52.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.76,0:13:55.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why can't we match the culprit's voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.89,0:13:57.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.30,0:14:03.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said the only ones who hated Sumida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and\Ndidn't have an alibi were those three people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.72,0:14:05.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three people?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.39,0:14:08.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We only heard two people's voices.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.28,0:14:10.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Re-mem-ber!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.28,0:14:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The third suspect was a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.86,0:14:17.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit's voice that Sensei heard\Nsounded like a woman, so he was skipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.25,0:14:18.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.99,0:14:24.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kodama Ryuusuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the guy who got skipped, was a\Nformer high school baseball star that lit up the Koshien.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.12,0:14:28.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But because he injured his shoulder, he went undrafted.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.13,0:14:30.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like he's now working at a host club.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.67,0:14:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He still didn't give up his dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.42,0:14:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he was off work, he practiced with a\Nbaseball club team to give it one last shot, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.14,0:14:45.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He recently completely broke his shoulder,\Nforcing him to quit the club team.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.27,0:14:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.06,0:14:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked Detective Takagi about it afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.15,0:14:54.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, how about the other two?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.11,0:14:55.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.28,0:14:58.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first suspect, Kagitani Kikuna{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, is a freelance worker.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.03,0:15:00.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's the ex-leader of a ladies racing gang.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.99,0:15:04.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But because she caused a serious accident, she lost her license.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.75,0:15:07.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A ladies gang leader?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.41,0:15:08.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.46,0:15:12.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's said that if she calls for it, a hundred people will gather to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.75,0:15:15.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, isn't she the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.38,0:15:17.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who can say?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.72,0:15:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard that during her trial, she needed\Na lot of money to pay for compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.14,0:15:24.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the last person?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.77,0:15:30.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takimoto Ryouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the manager of a small\Nrestaurant, and the daughter of an entrepreneur.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.31,0:15:36.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems she was trying to get back the money\Nshe had lost on some counterfeit plate...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.86,0:15:42.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And had spent quite a fortune on lawyers in an\Nattempt to sue the now-murdered Sumida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.49,0:15:48.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, she skipped out on sleep to consult\Nwith her lawyers, so she caught a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.62,0:15:53.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was also wearing a mask on the day\Nshe was called to the police station.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.17,0:15:53.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mask?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.34,0:15:55.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.17,0:15:57.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was wearing the mask in order to disguise her voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.97,0:16:00.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought of that at first as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.38,0:16:03.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But masks these days are thin enough to preserve one's voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.55,0:16:06.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it didn't sound like her voice was obstructed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.81,0:16:10.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the culprit Sensei heard had a woman's voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.44,0:16:14.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If one of the two female suspects is the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.57,0:16:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't the woman with the mask sound extremely suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.90,0:16:21.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the thing I'm bothered about.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.78,0:16:27.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she only heard the voice, how can Sensei be sure it was the culprit's?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.83,0:16:29.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course she can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.79,0:16:35.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because that woman yelled "Listen up,\Njust hand it over, or I'll kill you-wayo!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.17,0:16:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Sensei said that the fleeing culprit had a full figure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.97,0:16:42.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the victim, Sumida Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was a woman too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.55,0:16:49.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the "I'll kill you-wayo" was said by Sumida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.03,0:16:50.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.23,0:16:54.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Threatening to kill someone could cause\Nthe opponent to retaliate out of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.19,0:17:00.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beyond that, with regards to the truck with the\N"09" that Sensei saw leaving the scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.82,0:17:02.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why can't we find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.20,0:17:09.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truck the Professor called when he helped his\Nfriend move the other day didn't have numbers on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.45,0:17:12.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you see the truck?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.16,0:17:14.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, but I asked him...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.96,0:17:17.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whether it had numbers on the side or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.09,0:17:22.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the truck belonged to a company called\N"OSAKA NICO-NICO TRANSPORTATION."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.47,0:17:25.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the company's name, not numbers,\Nthat was printed largely on the side.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.64,0:17:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Company's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.35,0:17:31.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Professor also said...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.27,0:17:37.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the truck driver got lost because he wasn't\Nfamiliar with Tokyo and his GPS wasn't working right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.69,0:17:41.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was already past 8:00 PM when they could\Nfinally start the moving—it was a real hassle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.78,0:17:43.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.32,0:17:47.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You look like you're thinking hard about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.32,0:17:49.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you realize something?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.08,0:17:52.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.54,0:17:55.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My cavity's been hurting so I'm pressing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.59,0:17:56.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cavity?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.71,0:17:59.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've been saying that since before summer vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.88,0:18:01.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to go to the dentist...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.34,0:18:03.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.42,0:18:07.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't trick us with that pose, just go to the dentist already.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.24,0:18:09.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.86,0:18:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.06,0:18:14.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Shiratori?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.44,0:18:17.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.94,0:18:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said I have nothing else to tell the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.78,0:18:23.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.03,0:18:26.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We investigated further afterward...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.61,0:18:31.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we could only conclude that no one else\Nother than those three could be the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.87,0:18:34.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'd like you to listen to their voices one more ti—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.58,0:18:35.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.58,0:18:37.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I say so already?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.96,0:18:42.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,None of their voices is the same as what I heard from the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.50,0:18:44.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or do you think I'm telling a lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.92,0:18:45.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.09,0:18:52.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a lie when I said I'm here to have\Nyou confirm the suspects' voices again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.77,0:18:55.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I came here just to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.85,0:18:58.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To clear up your misunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.94,0:19:01.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't misunderstand anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.03,0:19:04.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looking good!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.53,0:19:06.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go, Inspector Shiratori!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.11,0:19:12.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is, when we met during that\Nearlier case, it wasn't for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.04,0:19:16.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had met you long before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.33,0:19:21.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were the girl who scolded the shoplifters in that bookstore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.25,0:19:23.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bookstore?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.46,0:19:24.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shoplifters?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.80,0:19:25.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.17,0:19:29.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was deeply moved by that girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.30,0:19:31.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I decided to join the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.14,0:19:34.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After seeing how brave you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.47,0:19:36.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brave...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.26,0:19:38.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Police...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.77,0:19:40.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.81,0:19:41.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.52,0:19:46.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I'm sorry, but I don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.95,0:19:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, about that girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.11,0:19:53.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't me—perhaps you mistook me for Detective Sato?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.74,0:19:55.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.87,0:19:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, please excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.58,0:19:59.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.63,0:20:03.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.73,0:20:21.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.52,0:20:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be heading home now, so would you please lock up when you leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.78,0:20:27.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.11,0:20:29.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.49,0:20:30.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.18,0:21:01.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello, Teitan Elementary School.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.94,0:21:03.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry for the late call.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.69,0:21:07.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm with the police, is Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.86,0:21:09.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Kobayashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.44,0:21:12.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I have nothing else to say to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.95,0:21:18.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the truck you saw with the 0 and 9 on the side has been found.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.95,0:21:22.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We took some photos and were hoping you could identify them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.96,0:21:23.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.87,0:21:27.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you would please send them to me at a later date...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.13,0:21:30.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, the confirmation is needed immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.38,0:21:33.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already asked the security guard to let me inside the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.55,0:21:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.01,0:21:37.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then come to the staff roo—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.68,0:21:39.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about the music room?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.72,0:21:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is, I graduated from here and\Nused to be in the brass band club.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.02,0:21:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It felt nostalgic when I looked around the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.52,0:21:49.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.48,0:21:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll come to the music room then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.24,0:21:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great, I'll be waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.86,0:21:56.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's an old boy here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.37,0:21:59.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder when he graduated?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.33,0:22:01.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.50,0:22:03.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were in the same class?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.63,0:22:14.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.51,0:22:20.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the music room was renovated last year, and\Nthe walls and desks have all been replaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.39,0:22:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's there to be nostalgic about?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.73,0:22:27.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, his voice just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.44,0:22:28.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where have I...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.03,0:24:03.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you can prove that Sensei's testimony was correct...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.49,0:24:05.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she'll open her heart to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.16,0:24:06.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's there!?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.37,0:24:11.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was someone there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.50,0:24:16.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, a suspicious shadowy figure was watching us.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.33,0:24:42.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.59,0:24:44.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Giraffe
